headline: Jamie Dimon Says Economy Is Weakening
summary: JPMorgan Chase Chief Executive Jamie Dimon said he thinks the economy is weakening following revised labor data showing a slide in job growth.  Meanwhile, another JPMorgan executive, Doug Petno, who is co-head of the commercial and investment bank, said Tuesday that the bank’s big clients were seeming more optimistic recently.

headline: JPMorgan elevates three insiders as global investment banking chairs on M&A revival
summary: Howard Chen, Charlie Dupree and Fred Turpin - will join a senior team that provides strategic advice to some of JPMorgan's most important clients as the largest U.S. bank bolsters its investment banking division, a key driver of recent profits.  The lender beat estimates for second-quarter profit in July and its investment banking fees rose 7% to $2.5 billion, fueled by an increase in M&As and debt underwriting.
